<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="ch1-section-atmosphere" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Atmosphere</title>

  <p>
    An <term><xref ref="term-atmosphere">atmosphere</xref></term> is a fluctuating, mobile envelope of mainly gases,
    with some small liquid and solid particles distributed throughout the empty space between gas particles,
    that is loosely held around a <term><xref ref="term-celestial-body">celestial body</xref></term>
    like a planet by the body's <term><xref ref="term-gravitational-force">gravitational force</xref></term> (Fig. 1).
    A celestial body's atmosphere extends from its surface to some indefinite height above the surface.
  </p>

</section>